xyz.thepathfinder.android

Class ClusterListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • xyz.thepathfinder.android.Listener<Cluster>
      • xyz.thepathfinder.android.ClusterListener

  • public abstract class ClusterListener
extends Listener<Cluster>
    The ClusterListener interface gives developers access to notifications when a cluster is modified. These notifications include changes to commodity, sub-clusters, and transports. They also include route notifications and others.

      • subclusterUpdated

        public void subclusterUpdated(Cluster cluster)
        Invoked when a subcluster was updated from this cluster by a message. Note, this update doesn't recurse up the cluster tree. If the cluster "/default/c1/c2/c3" receives an update message, both cluster "/defautl/c1/c2/c3" and "/default/c1/c2" will receive this message. This is because "/default/c1/c2/c3 was modified by the received message, but "/default/c1/c2" was not modified.
        Parameters:
        cluster - the cluster updated.

      • subclustersUpdated

        public void subclustersUpdated(Collection<Cluster> clusters)
        Invoked when a sublcuster was updated from this cluster by a message. Note, this update doesn't recurse up the cluster tree. If the cluster "/default/c1/c2/c3" receives an update message, both cluster "/defautl/c1/c2/c3" and "/default/c1/c2" will receive this message. This is because "/default/c1/c2/c3 was modified by the received message, but "/default/c1/c2" was not modified.
        Parameters:
        clusters - the subclusters that belong to this cluster.
